<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="278" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1158,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,1158,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[305,572,1158,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<typeStatus box="[305,416,1158,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Adult male.
</emphasis>
Structure typical for 
<taxonomicName box="[820,965,1158,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[820,965,1158,1182]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Ochrotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Flint" box="[1036,1157,1158,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (1972) Studies of Neotropical Caddisflies, XIII: The Genus Ochrotrichia from Mexico and Central America (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 118, 1 - 28. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.118" type="journal article" year="1972">
Flint 
<number box="[1100,1157,1159,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) except body length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
(from tip of head to end of the folded wings). Length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[1005,1095,1194,1219]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
. General color uniform brown (in alcohol). Head without modification. Tibial spur formula: 
<number box="[886,921,1231,1255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1-3</number>
- 
<number box="[931,949,1231,1255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
. Metascutellum subpentagonal. Abdomen without visible modifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1158,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Male genitalia. Sternum IX with anterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation box="[860,998,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 A – C" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1601,1624]" captionTargetBox="[227,1354,205,1560]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,193,1581]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4 A – C. Ochrotrichia constricta sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[913,928,1303,1327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
A, 
<number box="[962,978,1303,1327]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
C
</figureCitation>
); tergum IX very short and trapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 A – C" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1601,1624]" captionTargetBox="[227,1354,205,1560]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,193,1581]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4 A – C. Ochrotrichia constricta sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,227,1339,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
B
</figureCitation>
), with posterior margin slightly convex. Inferior appendages long; rectangular with apex truncate in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[224,317,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 A – C" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1601,1624]" captionTargetBox="[227,1354,205,1560]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,193,1581]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4 A – C. Ochrotrichia constricta sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[280,296,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
C
</figureCitation>
); with long setae over all surface and spine-like setae on internal surface (
<figureCitation box="[1190,1285,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 A – C" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1601,1624]" captionTargetBox="[227,1354,205,1560]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,193,1581]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4 A – C. Ochrotrichia constricta sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[1246,1261,1375,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). Segment X tergum with basal portion oval, constricted mesally; basal portion with a sclerotized spine-like process on right side; apical portion of the tergum X hooked in dorsal view and directed ventrally in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1303,1374,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 A – C" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1601,1624]" captionTargetBox="[227,1354,205,1560]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,193,1581]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4 A – C. Ochrotrichia constricta sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[1359,1374,1447,1471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B-C). Phallus tubular and elongate; without processes; ejaculatory duct not protruding (
<figureCitation box="[1061,1130,1482,1507]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 A – C" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1601,1624]" captionTargetBox="[227,1354,205,1560]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,193,1581]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 4 A – C. Ochrotrichia constricta sp. nov. Male genitalia: A, ventral; B, dorsal; C, left lateral; D, phallus, dosal. Scale: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/229020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
Fig. 
<number box="[1114,1130,1483,1507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1158,1903]" box="[199,511,1518,1543]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Female and larva unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="278" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1158,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1554,1579]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[324,590,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constricta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,590,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Ochrotrichia constricta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[600,689,1555,1578]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is not placed in any species group, because it does not share the diagnostic features of any group. This new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bueno-Soria &amp; Holzenthal, 1998" authorityName="Bueno-Soria &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="1998" box="[932,1400,1590,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silva">
<emphasis box="[932,952,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[967,1020,1590,1614]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">silva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bueno-Soria" box="[1028,1400,1590,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" refString="Bueno-Soria, J. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W. (1998) Studies in aquatic insects, XIV: description of eight new species of Ochrotrichia Mosely (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae), from Costa Rica. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 111 (3), 604 - 612." type="journal article" year="1998">
Bueno-Soria &amp; Holzenthal, 
<number box="[1344,1400,1591,1615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the shape of the spine-like process on the right side of tergum X and its mesal constriction. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,299,1663,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constricta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,299,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">O. constricta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[308,400,1662,1687]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[308,400,1662,1687]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from this and other 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1026,1662,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Ochrotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[881,1026,1662,1686]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Ochrotrichia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the absence of a second process at the basal area of tergum X and almost uniformly rectangular shape of the inferior appendages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1297,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1158,1903]" box="[199,1297,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1734,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="278">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in reference of the remarkable mesal constriction on tergum X.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
